cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY. 

The paper presents an autonomous navigation system for robots in densely populated environments, which involves tracking social groups and joining the flow of a social group to facilitate navigation. This involves the use of deep neural networks for tracking social groups and collision avoidance. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as they are closely related to the methods used in the paper. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible categories as they are related to the use of deep neural networks and control systems in the paper.
